sql:
SELECT * 
FROM drawings 
WHERE status = 'rejected';

SELECT reviewer_name FROM reviewers 
WHERE reviewer_id 
NOT IN (SELECT reviewer_id FROM drawing_approvals);

external_knowledge:
'finalized' refers to drawings with a status of 'approved'; 'merely glanced over' means the drawings were accessed in 'view' mode; 'background on these viewers' includes their roles, qualifications, and contact information.;
The 'Engineering team' specifically refers to the department named 'Engineering' in the database.;
The 'types of files' correspond to the file formats of the drawings.;
'Individuals who viewed them' refers to the users who accessed the drawings in 'view' mode.;

- "Seeds" metaphorically refer to drawings;
- "Germinating" metaphorically refers to the draft stage;
- "Garden plots" metaphorically represent the drawings in the drawings table;
- "Tended solely by Alice Johnson" refers to drawings reviewed by Alice Johnson.

